description:
USN-4165-1 fixed vulnerabilities in Firefox. The update introduced various
minor regressions. This update fixes the problems.

We apologize for the inconvenience.

Original advisory details:

 Multiple security issues were discovered in Firefox. If a user were
 tricked in to opening a specially crafted website, an attacker could
 potentially exploit these to cause a denial of service, bypass security
 restrictions, bypass same-origin restrictions, conduct cross-site
 scripting (XSS) attacks, bypass content security policy (CSP) protections,
 or execute arbitrary code.
title: Firefox regressions
action:
After a standard system update you need to restart Firefox to make
all the necessary changes.
isummary: USN-4165-1 caused some minor regressions in Firefox.
